t: An Evening Prayer for Sanctification and Protection.
O*pn Lord,*s I call upon You; hasten to me! Give*ln ear to my voice when I call to You!
May*ln my prayer be counted as incense before You; The*ln lifting up of my hands as the evening offering.
Set*ln a guard, O Lord,*s over my mouth; Keep*ln watch over the door of my lips.
Do*ln not incline my heart to any evil thing, To*ln practice deeds of wickedness With*ln men who do iniquity; And*ln do not let me eat of their delicacies.
Let*ln the righteous smite me in kindness and reprove me; It*ln is oil upon the head; Do*ln not let my head refuse it, For*ln still my prayer is against their wicked deeds.
Their*ln judges are thrown down by the sides of the rock, And*ln they hear my words, for they are pleasant.
As*ln when one plows and breaks open the earth, Our*ln bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol.
For*ln my eyes are toward You, O God,*s the Lord; In*ln You I take refuge; do not leave me defenseless.
Keep*ln me from the jaws of the trap which they have set for me, And*ln from the snares of those who do iniquity.
Let*ln the wicked fall into their own nets, While*ln I pass by safely.
